The First Peace Hub in Egypt - Creating a Community of Peace Educators. We need your support in creating the first Hub for qualifying peace builders in Egypt.  The Hub is a physical and online space designed to bring together practitioners specialised in peace, to develop their knowledge and skills, discuss, and co-create new projects in order to strengthen their impact on the communities they work in. By supporting our project, you will be contributing to the development of a network of over 500 peace builders in Egypt who are tirelessly working in the field & are still lacking the resources that enable them to address the root causes of violence on the ground.  So... who are we? Our organization, Misriyati (My Egypt) , started in 2004 with the dream of creating a peaceful Egypt; one where all identities are appreciated and welcomed. We realized that the traditional spaces of learning, be it family or school are incapable (or sometimes unwilling) to educate us about: how to deal with diversity, how to communicate our needs and feelings peacefully, and how to solve our conflicts non-violently.  Throughout the past 16 years we have supported thousands of individuals, groups, and organizations to build their capacity to deal with diversity and to pursue peaceful resolutions to conflicts. We have worked with refugees, young people, children, teachers, religious leaders, and community leaders, amongst others. The topics of our workshops focus on: identity, gender, social inclusion, conflict transformation, nonviolent communication, and collaborative teamwork.  Why a Hub for Peace Educators? The Hub will help peace educators share and exchange their resources in a common space where they can support each other's learning and co-create impactful  peace building projects on the ground. By doing so, the Hub is envisioned to support the creation of a generation of highly qualified professionals in the field of peace and conflict transformation in Egypt. The Hub is also envisioned to attract young peace builders working on the causes of gender based violence, corporal punishment in schools, discrimination against refugees, and sectarian violence. Those professionals are expected to disseminate the knowledge and values of peaceful living in the different communities in which they work with.  Through sustaining the programs and events at the Hub and transparent media coverage, the Hub is expected to attract more and more people and build new partnerships and collaborations - which is vital for sustaining the Peace Hub impact on a long-term basis.  Who will benefit from the Hub?The Hub will directly benefit a network of over 500 currently practising peace educators from different communities in Egypt. These individuals will then diffuse their new skills and knowledge to the groups they work with in the form of workshops, sessions and presentations. This will contribute to more peaceful and educated communities in Egypt and a shift in society toward peace. Peace educators may include: facilitators and trainers working on peace building, or teachers who want to learn how to peacefully manage diversity in the classroom, and solve conflict; parents who are interested to raise your children in the values of peace; peace practitioners who seek support in designing or implementing peace-building projects; or just an Individual who is striking to apply of peace in their daily life. What does it look like in practical terms?! The Hub will offer the following activities to peace educators: 
TOT (Training of Trainers);  empowering junior peace educators from different parts of Egypt;
Monthly meet-ups for peace educators to exchange knowledge and discuss compelling issues related to their experience in the field; 
Regular short-term and long-term workshops in peace/conflict management ( offered by participating peace educators on:  managing diversity in classroom; nonviolent communication; peaceful parenting, conflict transformation, gender equality, inner peace, inclusive leadership, mediation, dialogue);
Dialogue sessions and movie nights open to the public, around contemporary issues related to peace & violence (i.e.; harassment, identity, citizenship, social integration of refugees, etc.);
Designing new methods and tools in peace education and sharing them on an online platform;
Documentation of success stories from the ground on peaceful coexistence & nonviolent conflict transformation, to be published in the Peace Hub's monthly newsletter. 
 Why are we crowdfunding? Because we believe in the power of human solidarity and our collective desire to promote peace in our world.  We believe in our collective ability to make the things we life. As young peace educators trying to establish a new field of knowledge and practice, we face a lot of challenges (as you can imagine), which we navigate with happiness and curiosity. But one thing we know for sure is that we are not alone, and we don’t have to carry the entire weight on our own.Through your support, we are seeking seed funding to the hub and sustain its activities for a year. We want to cover the main fixed costs of the Peace hub on its online and offline form. It will support the establishment of the online platform ( website development and facilitation of online trainings and dialogues ). It will also support part of the rent, the renovation and the tools in the physical space (hopefully after CORONA situation is over) . Human Resources needed for the hub will be contributed on and based on the mutual benefits that every member of the hub will exchange with others.  Our Perks!Please note that the currency used in the campaign is Hong Kong Dollars! We are very thankful for your effort to help, and as a gesture of our gratitude:- If you pay $100 HKD, Wohoo! You will get an invitation to one rocking Webinar on Non-violent Communication. You will be supporting the conduct of one workshop for 25 participants in the hub. - If you pay $200 HKD, get a glimpse of what is going on the ground! You will get an invitation to attend a One day workshop on Conflict Transformation at the hub. You will be supporting one month rent of the hub space. -If you pay $500 HKD, Youpee!! You will be recognized as one of our Top Peace Co-Creators in our website.  You will be supporting the design of 100 new educational tools & methods. - If you pay $1000 HKD, you are bringing about a new generation of Peace Educators! A space will be dedicated  you on our wall our new space in recognition for your generous support. You will be supporting the conduct of one TOT for 25 junior peace educators from all over Egypt.  Other Ways You Can Help: Support The Peace-Hub by your knowledge: 1- Propose ideas about workshops that can benefit fellow peace educators. 2- Share a technique or a tool that can help in the peace-building process. If can't make a contribution, please help us spread the word:1. Host a crowdfunding party at your facility.2. Share the campaign on your social media.3. Follow us on Facebook and Instagram and share our campaign updates:https://www.facebook.com/Peacehubegypthttps://www.instagram.com/peacehubegypt4. Get the word out using the #SupportPeaceEgypt#DonateForPeaceThank you for your support!Contact the team!For any questions or comments about our crowdfunding campaign, or to learn more about Misriytai or the Peace Hub please:Email us: info@misriyati.orgMessage us: www.facebook.com/Misriyati
